Test: Link and Text Formatting

        /* Reset for consistency */
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { 
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; 
            font-size: 16px; 
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 700px;
        }

        /* Typography */
        h3 {
            font-size: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        /* Links */
        a {
            color: #0066cc;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: #004499;
        }

        a:visited {
            color: #6611cc;
        }

        /* Text formatting */
        .strong {
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .emphasis {
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .code {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 14px;
            background-color: #f3f4f6;
            padding: 2px 4px;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }

        .strikethrough {
            text-decoration: line-through;
        }

        /* Special formatting combinations */
        .highlight {
            background-color: #ffeb3b;
            padding: 1px 2px;
        }



    Text Formatting Examples

    This paragraph contains various inline formatting: bold text, italic text, and inline code.

    Links can be formatted too: bold link, italic link, and regular link.

    More advanced formatting includes strikethrough text and highlighted text.

    Complex combinations: bold italic, bold code link, and italic code.

    Reference links: See the documentation for more details, or check the API reference.



